<TEXT>
a former employee of a sunnyvale defense 
contractor was ordered friday to stand trial for the shooting 
deaths of seven people during a 5hour rampage at the plant in 
february 
richard wade farley 39 a onetime software engineer at esl 
inc was scheduled to be arraigned aug 2 in superior court no 
trial date has been set 
santa clara county municipal court judge edwin pearce ordered a 
trial for farley at a preliminary hearing following nearly two 
weeks of testimony from police and esl employees who were present 
the day of the feb 16 massacre 
police say that farley burst into the esl plant feb 16 loaded 
down with weapons and fired at least 100 rounds killing seven 
people and wounding three including a former coworker who had 
spurned his romantic advances 
also friday prosecutor alan nudelman said he was adding three 
charges of attempted murder and reducing one attemptedmurder 
charge to assault with a deadly weapon 
with those changes farley would face seven counts of murder and 
five of attempted murder as well as charges of burglary vandalism 
and assault with a deadly weapon 
the additional charges follow the testimony of esl employees 
randall hemingway karen mackey and william drake that farley shot 
at them and missed during the siege 
the reduced charge relates to the shooting of esl engineer laura 
black whose rejections of farleys repeated advances were cited as 
the reason for the rampage last week a tape was played of 
farleys conversation with police the night of the siege in which 
he said that he wanted black to survive the attack so she would 
live with regret that she had rejected him 
i am convinced it was not his intent to kill laura black 
nudelman said that would have defeated his purpose 
nudelman said he decided not to ask black to testify at the 
hearing because farley is an emotional rapist who would have 
derived satisfaction from seeing her on the witness stand but he 
said he would most assuredly seek her testimony at his trial 
farley had been fired from the plant in 1986 in part for 
harassing black she eventually obtained a judges ruling shortly 
before the shootings ordering farley to stay away from her 
esl develops computer programs for various department of defense 
projects 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

