head of a factory run by a school in xinxiang city 
the report said li was detained last december as a suspect after 
a teacher at the school was splashed in the face with sulfuric acid 
wang weiying deputy head of the local police department 
instructed and joined the other five in beating li with an electric 
club and torturing him in other ways during 18 hours of 
questioning the newspaper said li died after the ordeal 
an autopsy found that li was injured on 30 places on his body 
the china daily said the autopsy concluded that li who had a 
heart condition died of heart failure from physical abuse 
wang received a life sentence while the other five received 
sentences ranging from two to 15 years the newspaper said 
the torturing of common criminals and those with suspect 
political backgrounds was widespread during the ultraleftist 
196676 cultural revolution but has since been banned 
however chinese legal officials acknowledge there are still 
incidents of police abusing their power and the official media 
occasionally spotlights cases where suspects are tortured by police 
