two proabortion nuns have elected to 
resign from their order and stand with women rather than remain 
part of a patriarchal roman catholic church 
we arent nuns anymore said barbara ferraro and patricia 
hussey said thursday announcing an end to their long battle with 
the vatican over their right to support abortion 
for us to stand with women we need to renounce the 
differences privileges and even limitations that are part of 
membership in a religious community in a patriarchal church they 
said in a resignation letter 
the two said they will remain in the church 
six weeks ago the sisters of notre dame de namur decided to 
drop expulsion proceedings against hussey and ferraro 
the two have been at odds with the order since oct 7 1984 
when they and 94 other catholics including 22 other nuns and four 
priests signed a statement published in the new york times saying 
there is a diversity of opinion about abortion within the church 
catholic leaders threatened the priests and nuns who signed the 
statement with dismissal if they didnt recant their statements 
all agreed except for hussey and ferraro whom the church 
repeatedly asked for a retraction 
the sisters of notre dame began dismissal procedures last 
january by issuing a formal canonical warning the nuns who run a 
homeless shelter in charleston responded in a letter saying 
your demands are really an attempt to silence our consciences and 
our public voices on the issue of reproductive rights for women 
a second and final warning was issued in february in june 
however the 184yearold order backed down because the action 
would not be in the best interests of the order and the 
catholic church 
vatican officials still had the option of disciplining the nuns 
but ferraro said she and hussey had not been forced to resign 
although the dismissal procedure played a part in their decision to 
leave 
the violence of the process used with us by the leadership 
the lack of respect and understanding of our motivation for the 
good of the whole church by many in the community are for us 
insurmountable barriers to the reconstruction of a positive 
covenant relationship the nuns resignation letter said 
for the first time in four years we are able to address the 
question of our future in the religious community in a free and 
noncoercive atmosphere they said 
sister catherine hughes general moderator of the order said in 
a statement from rome that she had received word of the nuns 
decision a few days ago 
sisters patricia and barbara have done what the situation and 
their own integrity demanded hughes said they know that the 
prayers of the sisters of notre dame will follow them into the 
future 
ferraro and hussey said they will continue to run covenant 
house a homeless shelter and continue to be active in prochoice 
groups 
