<TEXT>
a member of a nationalist fijian group was 
found shot to death today at his home apparently after 
accidentally firing a gun designed to look like a pen a police 
official said 
ratu jone veisamasama 50 a prominent member of the fijian 
taukei political group was found slain at his farm in coloisuva 
about seven miles outside of suva 
he first was reported to have been shot by an assailant but 
police said at a news conference that he apparently shot himself 
accidentally with a crudely made gun designed to look like a pen 
no one could have shot him and escaped without being seen 
from this and other evidence it appears it was accidental and 
selfinflicted said jimi koroi acting police commissioner 
the taukei nationalist movement promotes the supremacy of ethnic 
fijians over ethnic indians which outnumber fijians among the 
pacific island nations 715000 people 
the taukei vigorously supported two military coups led by brig 
gen sitiveni rabuka last year that toppled an indiandominated 
government suspended the constitution of the former british colony 
and declared the islands a republic 
