<TEXT>
a boat that gained notoriety last summer for 
broadcasting rock music off the new york coast has been detained in 
boston harbor by the us coast guard as it was trying to reach 
international waters 
the 200foot former fishing boat that housed the pirate station 
radio newyork international was ordered back to port july 16 due to 
a variety of operational and licensing problems coast guard 
spokesman greg creedon said thursday 
the boat which was moving toward the edge of the harbor when it 
was ordered to return must install several onboard safety items 
and obtain proper financial documents in case of a pollution 
accident creedon said the operators face a 25000aday fine if 
the boat is moved 
al weiner a spokesman for rni said he hopes to comply with the 
coast guard orders and have the vessel on the seas later this 
summer 
the boat was seized by the coast guard about four miles off long 
beach ny after about a week of rni broadcasts last july during 
the seizure the radio transmitter and other equipment were 
damaged weiner said from his new york office on thursday 
charges of operating an illegal station against weiner and disc 
jockey ivan rothstein were eventually dropped 
they had said rni was created to protest the conformity in new 
york radio programming 
the boat has been fitted with about 25000 worth of radio and 
nautical equipment weiner said adding that hed like to bring the 
boat back off the coast of long island and create a format similar 
to last years program 
