<TEXT>
rescuers worked frantically today to locate more 
than 100 people missing from a boat that sank after hitting a rock 
in a southwest china river an official report said today it said 
four people were killed 
sixteen crew members and 132 passengers were rescued after the 
accident thursday china news service said in a report appearing in 
hong kong newspapers 
the survivors included 129 men and 19 women the news service 
said in a report from chengdu the capital of sichuan province 
about 930 miles southwest of beijing six people required 
hospitalization 
sichuan government officials were quoted in the report as saying 
rescue work was difficult because the accident occurred in a remote 
area and the rivers tide was high 
the boat was heading north from yiban city to leshan when it 
struck the rock and sank at about 430 pm thursday in qianwei 
county about 116 miles south of chengdu the report said 
the news service did not say how fast the boat was going and did 
not give the depth or width of the river at the site of the 
accident 
many people got on and off the passenger boat along the route 
making it difficult for officials to determine the exact number of 
passengers on board when the vessel sank 
the boats capacity was 324 and initial estimates placed the 
number of people on board at about 260 china news service said 
the report said it was not clear if the boat was carrying 
passengers from outside china 
the leshan foreign affairs office contacted by telephone from 
beijing said that sichuan governor zhang haoru and vice governor 
ma lin had gone to the scene but that no details were immediately 
available 
a chongqing central shipping administration official also 
reached by telephone from beijing said the boat belonged to the 
leshan branch of the chongqing shipping co 
he said the company had sent people to the scene but because of 
distance and poor communication they did not expect to have any 
details until saturday 
chinas official xinhua news agency said 115 people were missing 
and 131 people were rescued including five crew members and four 
bodies were pulled from the min river a tributary of the yangtze 
soldiers and militiamen were continuing rescue efforts it said in 
a terse report 
chinas last major boat accident occurred in april 1987 when 
two passenger ships collided in a dense fog on the yangtze river in 
sichuan province killing 18 people and injuring 21 
</TEXT>
