without resolving the dispute that has sparked demonstrations in 
chicago and bangkok 
the relic at issue called a lintel or crosspiece over a door 
or window is titled birth of brahma with reclining vishnu on a 
makara 
the 2feetlong by 3feetwide lintel depicts the hindu god 
vishnu reclining on water and dates to cambodias khmer dynasty 
from 8051250 ad 
it is the only important original piece missing from the 10acre 
khmer temple of phnom rung in the northeastern buri ram province 
near the cambodian border 
we will probably put a sign at the temple where the lintel 
should be so tourists including americans will know it was 
taken that we asked to give it back and that they the art 
institute would not the prince added 
