<TEXT>
a federal appeals court has overturned a judges 
ruling combining 35000 asbestosrelated lawsuits against a company 
a threejudge panel of the 11th us circuit court of appeals 
said wednesday that consolidating the suits would slow resolution 
of the cases 
us district judge robert l vining jr last month consolidated 
the personal injury lawsuits against raymark industries inc at the 
companys request creating the biggest asbestosrelated injury 
case ever 
more than 100 plaintiffs had objected to having their lawsuits 
consolidated saying none of them had been notified about the move 
according to court records they also argued that the evidence did 
not justify the action 
in overturning the consolidation decision the appeals court 
said the courts order which essentially moves their cases back 
to square one could hardly place petitioners in a more drastic 
predicament 
raymark has been the target of 70000 asbestos lawsuits 
involving 82000 people during the past 10 years the suits claim 
people developed asbestosrelated diseases after exposure to 
insulation and other raymark products 
half the cases have been resolved by trial settlement or 
dismissal 
raymark which expects 65000 more cases to be filed during the 
next decade sought to have the suits combined in a class action 
because the separate claims were depleting the companys insurance 
coverage 
