hearings to determine what penalties to impose for brazils alleged 
trade infractions 
white house spokesman marlin fitzwater said the hearings would 
determine what products would be subject to sanctions 
he said brazil eliminated patent protection for pharmaceuticals 
in 1945 and for pharmaceutical processes in 1969 
the president acted at the request of the pharmaceutical 
manufacturers association a washingtonbased trade organization 
fitzwater said us companies lose an estimated 36 million a year 
because of brazilian policies that permit unahtorized copying of 
pharmaceutical products and processes that were invited by us 
firms eighteen of the associations members do business in brazil 
they claim losses including lost export sales unrecovered research 
costs and reduced profit margins 
today was the deadline for the administration to complete its 
investigation of the charges 
reagan said his action was part of a threeyear campaign by the 
united states to challenge infringement of its intellectural 
