consumer prices rose at a moderate annual rate 
of 42 percent in june with the effects of the farm belt drought 
showing up clearly only in poultry and egg prices the government 
reported friday 
the labor department said retail prices overall rose just 03 
percent last month the same as in may food price rises held to a 
06 percent gain despite the biggest surge in poultry and egg 
prices since august 1986 when the nation was in the midst of the 
another drought 
offsetting increases on grocery shelves were a 02 percent 
decline in energy prices and a 03 percent drop in clothing costs 
id say the report is good news it clearly shows that 
inflation is not getting out of hand it has accelerated over the 
