stationary thunderstorms that were part of a large area of slowly 
moving showers and thunderstorms that formed ahead of a cold front 
along the atlantic coast states 
wilmington nc got a record 649 inches of rain for the date 
well over the former record of 388 inches set in 1877 
the water flooded street drains in downtown wilmington stalling 
cars and tying up traffic 
