by reporting unfavorably on police activities forced removals of 
poor blacks and labor disputes in rural areas that are not covered 
regularly by south africas mainstream press no criminal charges 
have been laid against the small agencies or their reporters but 
some journalists have been detained 
by law and custom apartheid establishes a racially segregated 
society in which south africas 26 million blacks have no vote in 
national affairs the 5 million whites control the economy and 
maintain separate districts schools and health services 
