<TEXT>
american brands inc said thursday its secondquarter profit 
climbed 44 percent while another food and tobacco concern rjr 
nabisco inc said its profit rose 18 percent for the quarter 
consumer products giant kraft inc the sale of its duracell 
battery division helped spark a sevenfold increase in its 
secondquarter earnings and colgatepalmolive co said its profit 
rose 17 percent from a year ago 
american brands headquartered in old greenwich conn said its 
net income for the quarter ended june 30 soared 44 percent to 
1546 million or 157 a share from 1074 million or 94 cents 
a share in the yearago period 
revenue jumped 27 percent to 249 billion from 196 billion in 
the second quarter of 1987 the figures include subsidiaries 
purchased from eii holdings inc in february in a deal valued at 
27 billion 
among the companys core businesses tobacco and distilled 
spirits put in a strong performance sales in the hardware home 
and office products unit more than doubled partly because of 
acquisitions 
for the years first half the company reported net income of 
305 million or 297 a share up 28 percent from 2382 million 
or 209 a share in the yearago period revenue totaled 540 
billion up 29 percent from 418 billion in the first half of 1987 
american brands main brands are lucky strike and pall mall 
cigarettes jim beam bourbon and gilbeys gin 
rjr nabisco based in atlanta reported its secondquarter 
profit rose to 354 million or 150 a share from 299 million 
or 116 a share in 1987 
the company said its sales rose 65 percent to 43 billion from 
4 billion in the second quarter of 1987 
rjr nabisco businesses include rj reynolds tobacco nabisco 
brands del monte foods and planters lifesavers 
the companys tobacco sales for the second quarter were 18 
billion up 75 percent from 17 billion in 1987 income from 
operations rose to 496 million a 76 percent increase from 461 
miullion the prior year 
the companys food business division achieved second quarter 
sales of 25 billion an increase of 59 percent from 23 billion 
in 1987 income from operations rose to 271 million up 14 percent 
from 238 million 
for the first six months of the year rjr said it earned 627 
million or 259 a share on revenue of 808 billion compared 
with a profit of 519 million or 2 a share on revenue of 751 
billion a year earlier 
kraft based in glenview ill reported net income of 785 
million or 610 per share in the second quarter compared with 
113 million or 83 cents a share for the same period a year ago 
sales increased 13 percent to 28 billion from 24 billion in 
the second quarter of 1987 kraft said 
the results include a 686 million aftertax gain from the june 
24 sale of duracell to a group led by kohlberg kravis roberts amp co 
excluding a total gain of 658 from that transaction and other 
discontinued operations krafts net income for the quarter totaled 
1273 million 
krafts largest division us consumer foods had sales of 12 
billion to lead all units in revenue production while the us 
commercial foods division showed the greatest improvement with a 21 
percent increase in sales to nearly 882 million 
for the first half of 1988 kraft had net income of 9035 
million or 7 per share compared with 265 million or 194 per 
share for the first half of 1987 
firsthalf revenues increased 145 percent to 54 billion from 
47 billion 
colgatepalmolive maker of soaps toilet and health care 
products and pet food reported net income of 655 million or 96 
cents a share up 17 percent from 561 million or 82 cents a 
share in the second quarter of 1987 
sales for the new yorkbased colgate totaled 119 billion up 9 
percent from 109 billion a year ago 
the company noted that profits from its household and personal 
care operations showed strong gains overseas specialty marketing 
sales were boosted by increased sales at hills pet products which 
recently began advertising nationally 
for the first six months net income rose 16 percent to 1309 
million or 191 a share from 1125 million or 162 a share in 
the yearago period revenue totaled 233 billion up 12 percent 
from 208 billion in the first half of 1987 
