<TEXT>
the fashion channel network inc which 
sells clothes through cable television said friday it has filed 
for court protection from its creditors under chapter 11 of the 
federal bankruptcy law 
the fashion channel said it was the result of severe liquidity 
problems but didnt supply financial data 
the company said it was negotiating an arrangement with a third 
party to continue the companys purchasing and sales operations 
and intended to keep distributing the program through present cable 
systems 
the company also is discussing investments by third parties it 
said 
according to information published earlier this year by the 
cabletelevision advertising bureau inc the fashion channel was 
carried on cable systems that had 77 million subscribers 
